## Implementation Guidelines

### 1. Mobile First
Always start with mobile styles and use `@media (min-width: ...)` to scale up.

### 2. Consistent Spacing
Use the defined spacing scale and utility classes for consistency.

### 3. Flexible Layouts
Use flexbox and grid with responsive breakpoints to ensure layouts adapt properly.

### 4. Zoom Compatibility
- Use `rem` units for fonts and spacing
- Avoid fixed pixel widths for containers
- Test zoom levels from 50% to 200%

### 5. Performance
- Use CSS custom properties for consistent values
- Minimize media query repetition
- Use efficient selectors

### 6. Accessibility
- Ensure sufficient touch targets (minimum 44px)
- Maintain readable text sizes at all zoom levels
- Provide adequate contrast ratios

